==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cosmorama
<hw>Cos`mo*ra"ma</hw> <pr>(k?z`m?-r?"m? ⟦or⟧ -r?"m?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>ko`smos</grk> the world + <grk>"o`rama</grk> a
sight, spectacle, fr. <grk>"ora^n</grk> to see.]</ety> <def>An
exhibition in which a series of views in various parts of the world is
seen reflected by mirrors through a series of lenses, with such
illumination, etc., as will make the views most closely represent
reality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

